00:20:13,217 --> 00:20:19,279
So what we did was add hero powers, which is a thing that you can do every turn that costs 2 mana

267
00:20:19,859 --> 00:20:25,200
that is not as powerful as a card, but is still a very useful thing to do, and also very class specific.

268
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:30,161
So if I have 3 mana and I have a hero power, I can either use the 3 mana card,

269
00:20:30,301 --> 00:20:34,182
or use my 1 mana card and use my hero power, or maybe I just use my hero power.

270
00:20:34,762 --> 00:20:37,843
And this is only in the simple case, but it's really an example of us.

271
00:20:38,363 --> 00:20:42,687
wanting to make sure that there were a lot of tactical depth and a lot of tactical choices

272
00:20:43,067 --> 00:20:45,469
as sort of as you were playing the game and we put hero powers in

273
00:20:45,489 --> 00:20:49,092
to do that as well as a few other things but that was the primary reason.

274
00:20:51,254 --> 00:20:54,957
This is a slide that will jump back a little bit to the simplicity slide.

275
00:20:56,815 --> 00:21:04,097
When we are making a card, we have sort of a general rule, which is if someone new reads that card for the first time,

276
00:21:04,757 --> 00:21:10,039
and they do not understand it immediately, they have to stop and parse it,

277
00:21:10,539 --> 00:21:16,982
then that card is probably too complicated, and either we go back and we spend a lot of time wordsmithing that card

278
00:21:17,002 --> 00:21:20,503
to make sure that that effect is something that you can instantly understand,

279
00:21:20,523 --> 00:21:23,824
or in a lot of cases, we actually went through and we just...

280
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:29,966
junked that card or that idea or changed it in some way to make it easily understood and

281
00:21:31,006 --> 00:21:36,208
Actually as a quick aside parse is a word that I use a lot when we're talking about the team and for me that means

282
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:41,409
does the player who's reading the whatever the text is have to actually stop and

